.TH SAVG\-EMISSION 1 "26 May 2009"
.SH NAME
savg-emission \- SAVG ToolBox: emission
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B savg-emission r g b/default
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I savg-emission
sets the emission color for \fIsavg\fP files (\fISAVG ToolBox\fP).  It 
accepts input from
.I stdin
and outputs to
.I stdout.
If invalid arguments or no arguments are given, 
then 
.I savg-emission
prints usage information and terminates.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \   savg-emission val val val or savg-emission default
Accepts floating 
point numbers from 0 to 1 and defaults to 1.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B savg-emission 0.5 0.2 0.1 < in.savg > out.savg
Reads from 
.I in.savg
and set the emission to 0.5,0.2,0.1.  Then outputs to 
.I out.savg.
